cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language inference, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a model that uses bidirectional LSTM and attention mechanism, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model also involves parameter optimization, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the model is evaluated on a dataset of textual entailment, which is a task related to natural language understanding and could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing textual data.
